<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-07-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-07-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="407" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d407">
                        <head>407. Memorandum From President <persName corresp="#p_KJF1" type="from">Kennedy</persName> to His Special Assistant for National Security
                            Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_BMG1" type="to">Bundy</persName>)<note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d407fn1">Source: Kennedy Library,
                                National Security Files, Countries Series, Laos: General,
                                7/1/62–7/16/62. The memorandum was not signed or initialed by
                                    <persName corresp="#p_KJF1">Kennedy</persName>. <persName corresp="#p_BMG1">Bundy</persName> wrote the following note on
                                the source text: “done &amp; understood.”</note></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Washington</placeName>,
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1962-07-03">July 3,
                                1962</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I do not want any further assistance to go to the Laotian Government
                            unless it is cleared here first.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>